Femi Fani-Kayode, former Minister of Aviation has reacted to the death of Senator Buruji Kashamu. Kashamu, a former Ogun East Senator died of COVID-19 complications on Saturday. The development was confirmed by former Bayelsa East Senator, Ben Murray-Bruce via his verified Twitter handle. However, Fani-Kayode expressed shock over the death of Kashamu. In a tweet, the former minister wrote: “Shocked and saddened to hear about the passing of my friend and brother Senator Buruji Kashamu as a result of Covid-19. “May the Lord honor and reward him with a place in heaven and may He forgive him of all his sins. RIP my old friend. “You fought a good fight and we shall miss you.”